* Miss World 2002 beauty pageant was held on the same date as Miss Nepal 2002, Malvika Subba was unable to compete at the international competition.

== Regions and subtitles at Miss Nepal ==

There is an unofficial formula to determine the states and regions represented in Nepal. The base number of contestants over the last decade has been 19–20, which can be increased or decreased by the pageant&#x27;s management.

List of subtitle award winners is as follows. The subtitles may vary with different editions of the pageant.

===Official states (20)===
  * Denotes that state has a preliminary pageant – which may or may not still be held – as of 2014 only Biratnagar, Chitwan, Dharan, Itahari, Jhapa and Pokhara held preliminaries.

  ** Denotes that state has been represented through Miss Purwanchal. Additionally, Miss Chitwan and Miss Pokhara hold their own individual pageants.

  *** Denotes that final audition held in Kathmandu selects the contestants who will compete in the final event.

===Official regions (5)===
*Kathmandu Valley, , Nepal Bhasa: स्वनिगः, Capital valley of Nepal includes Bhaktapur, Kathmandu, Kirtipur and Lalitpur.)
*Chitwan Valley, Southwestern valley of Nepal includes Chitwan, Makwanpur and Nawalparasi.)
*Pokhara Valley, , Western valley of Nepal includes Pokhara and Lekhnath.
*Eastern Region, , Eastern Region of Nepal includes Biratnagar, Dharan, Itahari and Jhapa.)
*Far-Western Region, Far Western Region of Nepal includes Dhangadhi and Mahendranagar, Dadeldhura, Baitadi, Bajhang, Darchula, Doti, Achham.

Biratnagar, Dharan, Itahari and Jhapa are regions of Eastern Region and are titles handed out at the Miss Purwanchal preliminary. As of 1995 Pokhara has its own preliminary through Miss Pokhara beauty pageant for the women of Gandaki Province.

Together, these 20 regions form the &quot;base&quot; of the Miss Nepal contest. However, at times other regions and territories have been represented. However, many times the pageant has been criticized for having lack of diversity interns of selection of candidates. Due to the reason that many girls from Kathmandu Valley are represented and are consistent in the pageant per year which resulted in the most winners from the Kathmandu Valley. However, since 2013, the pageant has decided to include more candidates from outside the Capital Valley.

== International franchise titles ==
Miss Nepal sends delegates to participate in 3 of the Big Four international beauty pageants as of 2024. Note that the year designates the time Nepal has acquired that particular pageant franchise.

Current franchise:
* &quot;Miss World&quot; (1997–present)
* &quot;Miss Earth&quot; (2002–present)
* &quot;Miss International&quot; (2000, 2005, reacquired in 2010–present) 
Previous Franchise:
* &quot;Miss Universe&quot; (2017–present) (on 2020 Miss Vibhaa took the franchise till 2023 headed by Uddhab Adhikari, The contest now under Global Glamour Venture P.Ltd. headed by Sangita Puri)
* &quot;Miss Supranational&quot; (2014, 2018–present)(The contest now under Sanurvi International Org. headed by Santosh Upadhyaya)
* &quot;Miss Asia Pacific International&quot; (1994–2017)

==Representatives at Big Four pageants==

The following women have represented Nepal in the Big Four international beauty pageants, the four major international beauty pageants for women. These are Miss World, Miss Universe, Miss International and Miss Earth.

===Miss Universe Nepal===
::&quot;Miss Nepal used to send a Miss Nepal to Miss Universe from 2017 to 2019. In that year Nagma Shrestha was directly nominated by Miss Nepal Organization without any competition as the first Miss Nepal Universe in the special occasion of 23rd Anniversary of Miss Nepal, Hidden Treasure.&quot;
::&quot;In 2020 the new org. called Miss Vibhaa debuted to select the winner to the Miss Universe pageant. This organization was under Uddhab Adhikari directorship (&quot;Umanga Creation&quot; 2020-2023).&quot;
::&quot;As of 2024, new organization, Global Glamour Venture P.Ltd. is responsible for organizing Miss Universe Nepal with Sangita Puri as National Director.&quot;
::&quot;On occasion, when the winner does not qualify (due to age) for either contest, a runner-up is sent.&quot;

===Miss World Nepal===

::&quot;After the local franchise for the Miss World pageant in 1997, Miss Nepal have started to send its winner. In 2002, the pageant was held in December which was after the Miss World 2002, hence the Miss Nepal 2002 winner, Malvika Subba missed the opportunity to represent Nepal in the Miss World pageant. On occasion, when the winner does not qualify (due to age) for either contest, a runner-up is sent.&quot;

===Miss Earth Nepal===

===Miss International Nepal===

::&quot;Before 2010, Miss Nepal International was organised by different company which produced winners that were represented in Miss International beauty pageant. But since 2010, Hidden Treasure bought the franchise to Miss International and now sends delegate from the annual Miss Nepal beauty pageant.&quot;

==Minor pageants representatives==
===Miss Supranational Nepal===
&quot;In 2016, Pooja Shrestha represented Nepal at Miss Supranational 2016. After two years, Miss Nepal began to send delegates regularly to Miss Supranational from 2018 when Mahima Singh was appointed as Miss Nepal Supranational. Since 2021, the delegate for Miss Supranational is seleceted by Mister and Miss National pageant by Santosh Upadhyay, National Director, Sanurvi International P.Ltd.&quot;
===Miss Asia Pacific Nepal===

::&quot;From 1994 to 1997, the Miss Nepal pageant was held to select the representative of the Nepal to the Miss Asia Pacific Pageant. In 1997, Jharana Bajracharya was crowned as Hidden Treasures Miss World Nepal 1997 winner who was sent to Miss World 1997 and Kathmandu Jaycees Miss Nepal where Nilima Gurung took the crown and went to Miss Asia Pacific 1997. After 1997, Miss Nepal Beauty Pageant started to hold the local franchise for the Miss World Pageant and the 1st runner-up was sent to the Miss Asia Pacific contest until 2005. The Hidden Treasure reacquired the franchise for 2016-2017. Since 2018, GEE Nepal Pvt. Ltd. is responsible for selecting &#x27;Miss Asia Pacific Nepal&#x27;.&quot;

==Other pageants==

===Miss North America Nepal===
The first ever Miss Nepal USA was held, in August 2011 and was organized by Event Planet Inc. Since 2014, there has been introduction to new special awards of Miss California Nepal, Miss New York Nepal and Miss Texas Nepal as the winners of regional states which were equivalent to 3rd runner-up spots. Since 2019, the Miss Nepal US Organisation stopped giving the special regional awards.

===Miss Hong Kong Nepal===
Miss Nepal Hong Kong was held in 1998 in favor of giving a platform for Nepalese teenagers to women in Hong Kong to build up their confidence and self-esteem. Factually, since Hong Kong&#x27;s life is hectic and also because of internal issues, Miss Nepal Hong Kong has had ups and downs: 1998 (was held), 1999 (canceled), 2000 (was held), 2001 (was held), 2002, 2003, 2004 (canceled), 2005 (was held). Consequently, Miss Talent Hunt Hong Kong Nepal (Mega Model) was replaced by Miss Nepal Hong Kong from 2006 to 2009 organized by Laxmi Rai (Lara), Mamita Gurung (Miss Hong Kong Nepal 2000), and Tara Subbha. It followed up organizers from 2008 (Basanti Pun and Sushmita Gurung) because of some internal issues. However, in 2010 since Miss Talent Hunt HK Nepal was transformed into an international pageant, it withdrew itself from Miss Nepal Hong Kong. After a long decades, fortunately, in 2011, the 5th Miss Nepal Hong Kong was held on 3 August 2011.

