<doc id="897710" wikidata="Q7067759" url="?curid=897710" title="Nu da șpagă">
<text>Nu da şpagă (&quot;Don&#x27;t Bribe&quot; in Romanian) is a national anti-corruption campaign launched in Romania in 2004 to deal with the problem of corruption in that country. The campaign is co-ordinated by Transparency International with the support of the European Union, which Romania joined in 2007. Corruption has been a problem in Romania since Communist times, but the situation has recently improved.

==External links==
* &quot;Nu da şpagă&quot; official site</text><links>
